        public SessionValue<Req,Res> getSession(SessionId id)
        Description copied from interface: SessionManager
        Returns the SessionValue based on the SessionId provided. If multiple values exists for the same key, only the head SessionValue element will be retrieved. This is somehow similar to peek() in Queue based implementations. The ordering is guaranteed by the SessionValue index.
        Specified by:
        getSession in interface SessionManager<Req extends AbstractRequest,Res extends AbstractResponse>
        Parameters:
        id - The SessionId instance to be used as the lookup key.
        Returns:

      • register

        public SessionId register(RequestDetails<Req,Res> requestDetails)
        Description copied from interface: SessionManager
        Registers the request to the session registry. This should be used once a request has been delivered via the underlying transport. If the same request type already exists in the registry, it will not replace the existing, rather it will be placed within the same collection under the same SessionId.
        Specified by:
        register in interface SessionManager<Req extends AbstractRequest,Res extends AbstractResponse>
        Parameters:
        requestDetails - A RequestDetails instance containing the details of the request.
        Returns:
        A SessionId if the request has been successfully registered.

      • unregister

        public boolean unregister(SessionId id)
        Description copied from interface: SessionManager
        Removes the associated session from the registry (if available) using a SessionId instance. This will try to retrieve the existing SessionValue from the registry using the id provided. If multiple sessions exists for this id, then only the top SessionValue will be removed.
        Specified by:
        unregister in interface SessionManager<Req extends AbstractRequest,Res extends AbstractResponse>
        Parameters:
        id - The SessionId instance to be used as the lookup reference for the session.
        Returns:
        true if the operation has been successful.
